# Monoceros global env (monoceros-config.env)
#
# Secrets shared across ALL your containers. This file is gitignored and
# never committed. Values here are the fallback; a per-container
# container-configs/<name>.env overrides them for that one container.
#
# Format is plain KEY=value, one per line, no quotes, '#' starts a comment.
#
# ===================================================================
# Git provider tokens (private repo clone/push + gh/glab auth)
# ===================================================================
#
# Monoceros clones and pushes private repos, and authenticates the gh /
# glab CLIs inside the container, from a Personal Access Token. Nothing
# (no gh/glab/git) needs to be installed on the host for this.
#
# Variable name:  GIT_TOKEN__<PROVIDER>_<LABEL>
#
#   PROVIDER is GITHUB or GITLAB. LABEL is any name you choose for the
#   account, so you can keep several tokens side by side:
#
#     GIT_TOKEN__GITHUB_CONCISO     (a work github.com account)
#     GIT_TOKEN__GITHUB_PICTOR      (a private github.com account)
#     GIT_TOKEN__GITLAB_CONCISO
#
#   On `apply`, Monoceros looks at your repos, finds the tokens for each
#   repo's provider, and uses the one (or, with several, asks you to pick)
#   and records the choice in the container's yml. So define every token
#   you have here once; each container picks the right one.
#
# Which token to create:
#
#   GitHub  ->  a classic token with the `repo` and `read:org` scopes
#               (the gh CLI needs read:org)
#               https://github.com/settings/tokens
#   GitLab  ->  a personal access token with the `api` scope
#               https://gitlab.com/-/user_settings/personal_access_tokens
#
#   Set an expiry. The same token covers git (clone/push) and the CLI
#   (PRs / merge requests / issues), so create it broad enough for the
#   work you do.
#
# Uncomment and set the ones you need:
#
# GIT_TOKEN__GITHUB_MYACCOUNT=ghp_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
# GIT_TOKEN__GITLAB_MYACCOUNT=glpat-xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
